## 9. QR Code System

### 9.1 Gate Pass QR (Hostel & Day Scholar)

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| QR Data | Firestore document ID from `gate_passes` |
| Logo | NIT Goa logo embedded in center (40×40px) |
| Size | 250×250px |
| Library | `qr_flutter` v4.1.0 |

**Lifecycle:**
1. Student generates QR → document created in `gate_passes`
2. Guard scans (1st time) → `scanCount` incremented to 1 (student exits)
3. Guard scans (2nd time) → document deleted (student re-enters)
4. `_watchPass` listener detects deletion → QR disappears from app
5. If not scanned → hidden from app after 12 hours (document remains in Firebase)

### 9.2 Leave QR

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| QR Data | Firestore document ID from `leave_requests` |
| Generated when | Warden approves the leave application |
| Deleted by | Student manually (typing "delete_qr") or Security Portal |

**Key behavior:**
- QR contains only the document ID — the guard's scanner reads full details from Firebase
- If extension is approved, the Firebase document is updated but QR code stays the same
- Same QR is valid for the entire leave duration including extensions

