## 10. Caching Strategy

### UserCache (Singleton)

```
Location: lib/services/user_cache.dart
Pattern: Singleton with in-memory cache
```

| Method | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `loadProfile()` | Loads from Firestore, caches in memory. Skips Firestore if already cached |
| `loadProfile(forceRefresh: true)` | Always reads from Firestore |
| `updateCache(data)` | Updates local cache without Firestore write |
| `clear()` | Clears cache (called on logout) |
| `profileData` | Getter for cached data |

**How it reduces Firestore reads:**
- Profile loaded once at login (`AuthGate`) with `forceRefresh: true`
- All subsequent screens read from `UserCache().profileData` — zero Firestore reads
- Profile save in `ProfileSetup` updates both Firestore + cache
- Logout clears cache

