## 14. Known Limitations & Behaviors

### 14.1 QR Code Behaviors
- Gate pass QR hidden from app after 12 hours regardless of scan count
- If student exits (1st scan) but doesn't return within 12 hours, QR disappears from app but stays in Firebase
- Student can generate a new QR after old one is hidden
- Unused gate passes pile up in Firebase (not auto-deleted)

### 14.2 Leave System
- Only one pending/approved leave request allowed per student
- Rejected leave requests auto-deleted after 2 days
- Extension can only be applied once per leave
- QR code doesn't change when extension is approved (just the Firebase document updates)

### 14.3 History
- Warden history shows last 7 days only
- Auto-cleanup deletes history entries older than 7 days from Firebase
- History persists even if student deletes their leave QR

### 14.4 Photo Storage
- Photos stored as base64 strings in Firestore (not Firebase Storage)
- Limited to 100 KB (Android) / 500 KB (Web) to stay within Firestore document size limits

### 14.5 Security
- `gate_passes` and `leave_requests` allow public read/delete (for Security Portal)
- `users` and `leave_history` require authenticated @nitgoa.ac.in email
- API keys are visible in `firebase_options.dart` (standard for Firebase client apps)

